The paper discusses transfer learning through deep neural networks in the field of question answering, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of transfer learning in different datasets and tasks, which involves machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with information retrieval and text classification, which are subfields of NLP, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses image-based datasets for evaluation, which involves computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
